  "description": "Dermal tissue: the protective outer tissue system that forms the boundary between a plant and its environment. All plant organs (roots, stems, leaves, flowers, fruits) are wrapped in dermal tissue, which serves as the primary barrier to water loss, microbial invasion, herbivory, and excessive ultraviolet radiation.",
